Namaste,

As I said before, the nyaasa people do today is merely a formality. 
Nyasa literally means placement. You *place* certain sound combinations 
in certain chakras (energy centers) in various body parts (e.g. tips of 
ring fingers, tips of little fingers, heart, top of head, between eyes 
etc).

If you touch a body part in a particular way and say the sound, will 
that really *place* that sound in that chakra? Will that chakra vibrate 
with that sound then? Of course, not.

Those who have been taught a procedure by somebody can follow what they 
are taught. Those who do not know need not worry.

Just as the streets and surroundings of your house may automatically be 
repaired if the Prime Minister of India decides to visit your house, 
various chakras in your subtle body will automatically vibrate with the 
correct sounds if the deity decides to express to you in some form or 
the other.

Building devotion and surrender is far more important and useful than to 
focus on technicalities and try to master them.

